{# English educational content templates #}

{# Understanding gut health section #}
{% macro gut_health_basics() %}
<div class="educational-section">
    <h4>Understanding Equine Gut Health</h4>
    <p>The equine gut microbiome is a complex ecosystem of trillions of microorganisms that play crucial roles in digestion, immune function, and overall health. A balanced microbiome supports:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Efficient fiber digestion and nutrient absorption</li>
        <li>Production of essential vitamins and short-chain fatty acids</li>
        <li>Immune system development and function</li>
        <li>Protection against pathogenic bacteria</li>
        <li>Maintenance of gut barrier integrity</li>
    </ul>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{# Microbiome importance section #}
{% macro microbiome_importance() %}
<div class="educational-section">
    <h4>The Importance of Microbiome Balance</h4>
    <p>Microbiome imbalances (dysbiosis) can result from various factors including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Antibiotic treatments</li>
        <li>Dietary changes or poor-quality feed</li>
        <li>Stress and environmental changes</li>
        <li>Illness or inflammatory conditions</li>
        <li>Age-related changes</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Early detection and intervention can help prevent more serious digestive and health issues.</p>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{# Key bacterial phyla information #}
{% macro key_phyla_info() %}
<div class="educational-section">
    <h4>Key Bacterial Groups</h4>
    <div class="phyla-info">
        <p><strong>Bacillota:</strong> Primary fiber digesters that break down cellulose and produce beneficial short-chain fatty acids.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Bacteroidota:</strong> Specialists in complex carbohydrate metabolism and vitamin synthesis.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Actinomycetota:</strong> Important for maintaining gut health and producing antimicrobial compounds.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Pseudomonadota:</strong> Includes both beneficial and potentially harmful bacteria; elevated levels may indicate inflammation.</p>
    </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{# Dietary recommendations based on results #}
{% macro dietary_recommendations(dysbiosis_category) %}
<div class="educational-section">
    <h4>Dietary Support Recommendations</h4>
    {% if dysbiosis_category == 'normal' %}
    <ul>
        <li>Continue current feeding program</li>
        <li>Maintain consistent feeding schedule</li>
        <li>Ensure access to quality pasture or hay</li>
        <li>Provide adequate fresh water</li>
        <li>Consider periodic probiotic supplementation</li>
    </ul>
    {% elif dysbiosis_category == 'mild' %}
    <ul>
        <li>Review and optimize current diet composition</li>
        <li>Increase high-quality fiber sources</li>
        <li>Consider probiotic supplementation</li>
        <li>Reduce dietary sugars and starches</li>
        <li>Ensure gradual dietary transitions</li>
        <li>Monitor for improvement over 2-4 weeks</li>
    </ul>
    {% else %}
    <ul>
        <li>Consult with veterinarian for comprehensive evaluation</li>
        <li>Implement therapeutic probiotic protocol</li>
        <li>Consider digestive support supplements</li>
        <li>Evaluate for underlying medical conditions</li>
        <li>Minimize dietary changes during recovery</li>
        <li>Monitor closely and retest as recommended</li>
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{# Management recommendations #}
{% macro management_recommendations(dysbiosis_category) %}
<div class="educational-section">
    <h4>Management Considerations</h4>
    {% if dysbiosis_category == 'normal' %}
    <p><strong>Maintenance Protocol:</strong> Continue current management practices. Consider annual microbiome screening to monitor long-term gut health trends.</p>
    {% elif dysbiosis_category == 'mild' %}
    <p><strong>Monitoring Protocol:</strong> Implement dietary modifications and retest in 6-8 weeks. Monitor for digestive symptoms and overall condition.</p>
    {% else %}
    <p><strong>Intervention Protocol:</strong> Veterinary consultation recommended. Consider comprehensive digestive health evaluation and targeted treatment plan.</p>
    {% endif %}
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{# When to contact veterinarian #}
{% macro veterinary_guidance() %}
<div class="educational-section important-box">
    <h4>When to Contact Your Veterinarian</h4>
    <p>Contact your veterinarian if you observe:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Changes in appetite or eating behavior</li>
        <li>Loose stools, diarrhea, or constipation</li>
        <li>Increased colic episodes</li>
        <li>Changes in body condition or weight loss</li>
        <li>Decreased performance or energy levels</li>
        <li>Any concerns about digestive health</li>
    </ul>
</div>
{% endmacro %}